    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\nI have enums, dicts and sometimes classes in my code. They contains constant values. During developement i want to see keys of constants.\n\nBut in runtime accessing structure not needed, just value.\n\nFor example eval `self.d[\"Acct-Status-Type\"][\"Interim-Update\"]` to `3`\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\nMark fuction typing as Eval (Custom type inherited from Final)\n\n```\ndef asConst(v) -> Eval:\n    return v\n\nprint(asConst(d[\"Acct-Status-Type\"][\"Interim-Update\"]))\n```\n\nCython converts it to something like define statement \n\n```\n#define asConst(d[\"Acct-Status-Type\"][\"Interim-Update\"]) 3\n```\n\nand my constants become constants in C code.\n\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
